**Class Definition and Header File**

We begin by defining the `UndergraduateStudent` class in a header file. This class will encapsulate the essential data members such as the full name, student ID, and GPA. The class will also include appropriate constructors, accessors, and mutators to ensure data integrity and encapsulation.

```cpp
#ifndef UNDERGRADUATESTUDENT_H
#define UNDERGRADUATESTUDENT_H

#include <string>

class UndergraduateStudent {
private:
    std::string fullName;
    std::string studentID;
    double gpa;

public:
    // Constructor
    UndergraduateStudent(const std::string& name, const std::string& id, double initialGPA);

    // Accessor methods
    std::string getFullName() const;
    std::string getStudentID() const;
    double getGPA() const;

    // Mutator methods
    void setFullName(const std::string& name);
    void setStudentID(const std::string& id);
    void updateGPA(double newGPA);

    // Method to display student information
    void displayProfile() const;
};

#endif // UNDERGRADUATESTUDENT_H
```

