**Implementation File**

The implementation file contains the definitions of the class methods. It ensures that the GPA is validated to be within a reasonable range (e.g., 0.0 to 4.0) and that the student ID is not empty. This guarantees the robustness of the data being stored.

```cpp
#include "UndergraduateStudent.h"
#include <iostream>

UndergraduateStudent::UndergraduateStudent(const std::string& name, const std::string& id, double initialGPA)
    : fullName(name), studentID(id), gpa(initialGPA) {
    if (gpa < 0.0 || gpa > 4.0) {
        std::cerr << "Invalid GPA. Setting GPA to 0.0." << std::endl;
        gpa = 0.0;
    }
}

std::string UndergraduateStudent::getFullName() const {
    return fullName;
}

std::string UndergraduateStudent::getStudentID() const {
    return studentID;
}

